Both nominee's to win office need to get a minimum of 75 to 80 million votes to win the Oval Office! The historical participation rate by Registered Voters is 58%! So it is anticipated that the most who will vote in the 2016 General Election will be 130 million and the least 110 million! As of today 51% don't want either candidate and 30% indicate they will vote for the Independent if he gets on State Ballots or most of them will stay home! Hillary has a 55% Unfavorable and Trump just hit a high no one in history has ever achieved a 70% And although Trump broke all records for Votes in the Republican Primary as of today Total Republican/Independent Primary Votes = 25,785,537 (Trump received 14,732,381) Total Democratic/Independent Primary Votes = 28,892,395 in total this represents less than 27% of Registered! Historically, 58% of Registered Voters go to the poles! There were 12 Caucus States where no votes were counted only delegates! In the General Election all those voters who were denied participation in those states get to go straight to their poles or mail their ballots in!
